Hampl Sees Czech Golden Era of Inflation Targeting, Tyden Says

-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 
2011-06-27T09:11:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-27/hampl-sees-czech-golden-era-of-inflation-targeting-tyden-says.html
Inflation in the  Czech Republic  is
well under control and the central bank is experiencing “golden
times” in meeting its inflation target, weekly magazine  Tyden 
reported, citing central bank Vice Governor Mojmir Hampl.  To contact the reporter on this story:
